        "comment": {
            "comments": [
                {
                    "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/13131103/comment/16340237",
                    "id": "16340237",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=jim.crist",
                        "name": "jim.crist",
                        "key": "jim.crist",
                        "avatarUrls": {
                            "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?ownerId=jim.crist&avatarId=33449",
                            "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&ownerId=jim.crist&avatarId=33449",
                            "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&ownerId=jim.crist&avatarId=33449",
                            "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&ownerId=jim.crist&avatarId=33449"
                        },
                        "displayName": "Jim Crist",
                        "active": true,
                        "timeZone": "Etc/UTC"
                    },
                    "body": "This looks to be because the cython code is wrapping `NumPyDtypeToArrow`, which expects a dtype object, but the objects being passed in aren't `dtype` objects.\r\n\r\n\u00a0\r\n{code:java}\r\nIn [8]: pa.from_numpy_dtype(np.dtype('U'))  # this is a dtype, works fine\r\nOut[8]: DataType(string)\r\n\r\nIn [9]: pa.from_numpy_dtype(np.unicode)  # not a dtype\r\nOut[9]: DataType(int8)\r\n{code}\r\nI'd like to take this on. Since the C++ signature is `PyObject`, should the conversion be done there or in the cython code? It's not clear to me the distinction between the cython and c++ python codebases.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=jim.crist",
                        "name": "jim.crist",
                        "key": "jim.crist",
