                            "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&ownerId=wesmckinn&avatarId=29931"
                        },
                        "displayName": "Wes McKinney",
                        "active": true,
                        "timeZone": "America/New_York"
                    },
                    "body": "It'd probably easiest to ensure that the input value is a dtype in Cython. For code that only touches the Python C API or Arrow API, there's no hard distinction between where to put code except what is more convenient (and generally keeping the Cython bindings as \"thin\" as possible). the C++ arrow/python code does not expose any of the C++ libraries' dependencies to keep the build system simple",
                    "updateAuthor": {
